               <objectContents>
                  <ab type="description">A worker in uniform is reparing a sewing machine (Strobel). He wears glasses and a coat, which is marked with the sign X on its pocket that contains pens and screwdrivers. There is also a guidebook entitled "Betriebsanleitung" hanging on a wall. In the first picture there is another worker with uniform next to him, observing the activity. In another picture, we see the right arm of a woman standing nearby. The space or the corner in which he works seems to be a repair section, judging by the tools, aparats, and cables that can be seen. Furthermore, in the background there are lights, posters, a hand-wasching place, an orman etc. </ab>
                  <ab type="comment">Danas 2/1973 gives the identity of this worker.</ab>
               </objectContents>
